Gordon Reid will retire as COO of TSX-listed gold miner Centerra at the end of the year, after more than 15 years with the company. Gordon joined Centerra in October 2004 and was VP for business development before moving to Kyrgyzstan in October 2007 to assume the role of president of Kumtor Operating Company. He served in that role until March 2009 before returning to Toronto to assume the role of VP for operations. He was promoted to his current position of VP and COO in 2013. Daniel Desjardins, president of Kumtor Gold Company, will succeed Gordon on January 1.